author: NewsWire
title: Spain seal Euro 2016 berth with emphatic 4-0 win over Luxembourg
text:
0 0 0 0 0 
London, Oct.10 (ANI): Defending champions Spain secured their place at the Euro Championship 2016 after claiming an emphatic 4-0 win over Luxembourg in their Group C qualifier clash. 
Santi Cazorla and the substitute Paco Alcacer scored a brace each to assure Spain of top spot in the section with a game to spare, the Guardian reported. 
Spain, which bagged the title in 2008 and 2012, are five points ahead of second-placed Slovakia. (ANI) Related Posts
